description: WARM AND INVITING! Beautifully updated home in the Candlewood section of Howell, this 4-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom split-level home has exceptional curb appeal and large fully fenced yard. This home features open living spaces across three distinct levels with room to entertain or relax. The lower level features a welcoming foyer with ample closet space, leading into a comfortable living room with a wood burning fireplace, nearby powder room, and direct entry to the 2-car garage.  The home's main level is hallmarked by a massive living/dining combination room with vaulted ceilings, near a spacious eat-in kitchen with stone flooring and sliding-door access to the backyard.  Completing the interior are 4 bedrooms and 2 updated full bathrooms, including a sizable master suite with ensuite full bath with radiant tile floor.  Begin planning for summer NOW and take full advantage of a true entertainer's backyard, boasting a large rear patio, in-ground pool, and considerable lawn space.  Fresh siding, newer windows, a Timberline roof, and solar panels complete the package.  Take advantage of an excellent school district and convenient location, near commuter access, downtown areas, and ocean beaches of the Jersey Shore!

The chef’s kitchen design include 42” cabinets, quartz counter tops and backsplash, under mount stainless sink, stainless steel appliances and recessed lights. This open concept space flows from kitchen to an over-sized living room with a quartz tile wrapped wood burning fireplace, perfect for entertaining or cozy winter nights at home. The large spa-style bathroom feature a frameless glass enclosed standing shower, hexagon tile flooring, custom built quartz seat, and a floating double vanity. Gorgeous 7” American Walnut flooring throughout, and multiple areas of additional lofted storage. Located downtown with easy access to NYC via PATH, Bus or Ferry! Professionally managed building, pets allowed, and laundry!

The upper level is just as impressive and features: the master suite with a his and her WIC and lavish full bath with big stand up shower with floor to ceiling custom tile, built in bench and built in shelves, a skylight, granite top double sink and extra cabinets; 3 additional bedrooms all with ceiling fans and updated full bath. Sit outside and relax or entertain in the park-like backyard surrounded by the mature tree's, sweeping lawns, paver patio and 2 storage sheds. Additional features: full basement, recessed lighting, central vac, whole house is wired for speakers, attic with pull down stairs, newer roof, new water heater, newer Anderson windows, newer heating and ac, 2 car garage and driveway parking and custom window treatments. Extremely private location yet close to shopping, restaurants and schools. This is truly an exceptional home that has been meticulously well maintained, beautifully updated and shows the true pride of ownership.

People passing through the Western Section take notice of this fine Colonial, not for its imposing size, but for its pleasing symmetry and gracious boxwood-lined lawn. Should any be lucky enough to step inside, they would be stunned to discover an interior just as spacious as any neighboring home with every detail, from doorknobs to bathtubs, painstakingly restored or carefully sourced to complement the original 1915 residence. A two-phase project with architect T. Jeffrey Clarke at the helm breathed new life into the original house, then vastly expanded the footprint out the back with the quality of Shulte Restorations work on full display. Uncommon nine-over-one windows were stripped and restored to smooth working order and then custom matched in the rear wing. Amish-crafted tiger maple cabinetry was finished on-site for a flawless fit in the mudroom, laundry room and, of course, the kitchen, which pulls everyone together like a magnet. Perhaps it’s the steady warmth of the massive range, just one of several imported Aga appliances, or the leathered granite island big enough to spread out the most abundant buffet. A family room wrapped in shiplap and a covered porch past a Dutch door offer casual spots to unwind, while the living room is decidedly more formal with Williamsburg-inspired paneling around a working fireplace. Five bedrooms have distinct amenities, such as dressing alcoves, that lend character and functionality, but none is as resplendent as the main suite with a remarkably airy bathroom with featured soaking tub. The finished, walk-out basement keeps games and rowdy fun as far as possible from the top floor study, a work-from-home sanctuary. This meticulously executed labor of love was a featured stop on The Historical Society of Princeton’s famous house tour. All of this sits perfectly positioned with Nassau Street just 4/10 of a mile away…come see!

Beautiful beachfront located on the now immensely popular "morning glory/evening splendor" coastline section of Sea Isle City. This stretch of beachfront homes is unique to the entire Cape May County coast. Homes at this location enjoy both morning sunrises directly over the Atlantic and unobstructed evening sunsets over the bay and its wildlife-filled wetlands. Some of the finest Sea Isle beachfront townhomes have been developed here in recent years to take advantage of those views and the resulting less crowded stretches of beaches found here. This is your opportunity to secure your place along this exclusive stretch of beachfront homes. The townhouse features true hardwood floors, a contemporary styled kitchen with carpenter-crafted cabinetry, extended granite counter space including a long center island, carpenter built-in benches with storage in the sunny great room, and fine finishes throughout. A large garage area with storage space on the ground floor also contains the entrance to the elevator which accesses every floor of the residence. The first floor features three bedrooms, each with their own ensuite access to separate bathrooms. The architectural design of this home incorporated the full ocean-sunrise-bay-sunset potential with a long living area extending the full length of the second floor. The space from the entertainment area on the beachside through the centrally located kitchen to the dining area on the bayside is one open area. However, the current owners ingeniously added a sliding barn door so that a dining area can also be cordoned off as its own space. To this "bay room" they added a built-in bench-and-storage on one wall flanked opposite by a granite counter wet bar with built-in refrigeration. The result offers an intimate space for dining or evening cocktails when the mood is right. A small deck on the bay side off this room is the perfect retreat for a guests to step away from the inside crowd to enjoy a magic sunset. Finally, this home offers an owners' bedroom that's a rare Sea Isle townhouse find. Instead of maximizing for number of bedrooms, the design of this home does not short-change the owner bedroom and instead dedicates the entire third floor to private quarters. A sunset deck in the rear is off a space the current owners utilized as an office, but would also be great as an exercise area, closet storage, yoga or meditation area, or additional media area. A large bathroom with a walk-in shower divides that section from the bedroom area. The bed side offers views of the ocean from both beachside windows and a sliding-glass door to a crow-perch on the southern corner of the home. This is a wonderfully well-built townhome on one of the most magnificent stretches of shoreline in NJ. It's ideally located where beaches are less crowded with fantastic views of both the ocean and the bay that can rarely be found simultaneously in the same home. The buyer looking for a special place in Sea Isle will not be disappointed.
